WEBVTT

00:01.667 --> 00:05.000
All right, Nick,
we believe in you, man.

00:05.453 --> 00:07.020
Tell us, what's in the cup?

00:07.088 --> 00:08.087
Ah, it's a hard one.

00:09.940 --> 00:10.974
It's a mini carrot.

00:11.826 --> 00:12.960
Onion and potato?

00:13.027 --> 00:14.294
Dumbest boy in all the world.

00:14.362 --> 00:15.896
How are you so bad
at Feely-Cup?

00:15.964 --> 00:17.297
You are awful at this game.

00:17.365 --> 00:18.966
Sea glass?
I'm overthinking it.

00:19.033 --> 00:21.467
If his life depended
on this, he would die.

00:21.534 --> 00:23.635
- Battery.
- When are batteries squishy?

00:23.703 --> 00:25.471
I'm just kidding, I'm kidding--
I know it's not a battery.

00:25.538 --> 00:26.805
I'm kidding. Feel, Nick.

00:27.374 --> 00:29.441
Nick, will you be paying
for bonus time?

00:29.509 --> 00:31.344
He can't;
He is all out of quarters.

00:31.411 --> 00:33.346
Uh, Nick?

00:33.413 --> 00:34.747
Your dad's here.

00:34.814 --> 00:36.215
Very funny, Schmidty,
but my concentration

00:36.283 --> 00:37.782
will not be broken.

00:40.051 --> 00:41.452
Hey-ya, Nickels.

00:43.689 --> 00:45.056
Come on, kid, bring it in.

00:45.124 --> 00:46.824
Come on!

00:46.893 --> 00:48.413
Hello, Mr. Miller.
Welcome to our home.

00:48.427 --> 00:49.794
- Feely-Cup?
- Oh, yeah.

00:49.862 --> 00:50.795
Bring it on.

00:53.265 --> 00:53.765
Watch this.

00:56.501 --> 00:57.134
Tampon...

00:58.996 --> 01:00.704
Wrapped in duct tape...

01:02.073 --> 01:04.108
And dipped...
in baking powder.

01:04.175 --> 01:06.110
- Is that what it is? Oh, it is.
- Boom!

01:06.177 --> 01:09.112
- Next level Feely-Cup.
- Hello, Mr. Miller.

01:09.179 --> 01:11.080
♪ Who's that girl? ♪

01:11.148 --> 01:12.815
♪ <i>Who's that girl?</i> ♪
♪ It's Jess. ♪

01:13.353 --> 01:17.320
<font color="#ff8c00">Sync & corrections by Alice</font>
<font color="#ff8c00"> www.addic7ed.com</font>

01:17.388 --> 01:19.188
This is a pleasant surprise.

01:19.256 --> 01:21.024
What brings you to Los Angeles, Dad?

01:21.091 --> 01:22.758
Let me just, uh, clean up a little bit.

01:22.826 --> 01:24.894
You know, I just thought I'd stop by.

01:24.961 --> 01:26.561
I'll sleep in your bed,
you can go on the couch.

01:26.629 --> 01:27.829
Sounds like us.

01:27.897 --> 01:29.497
Hey.

01:29.565 --> 01:31.433
So, what does Mr. Miller do?

01:31.500 --> 01:33.335
- Businessman. - A what?
- He's a con man.

01:33.403 --> 01:34.270
He is a con man.

01:34.271 --> 01:35.137
He is a damn business--
What are you talking about?

01:35.204 --> 01:36.371
- He's a con man.
- He's a businessman.

01:36.439 --> 01:37.639
Winston's obsessed with Walt.

01:37.706 --> 01:39.975
That moustache
first of all-- what?!

01:40.043 --> 01:41.809
It's like the world's
sexiest push broom.

01:41.876 --> 01:43.844
A con man like,
"What's the play?"

01:43.912 --> 01:45.579
The, uh, Ring-A-Doo
Johnnycakes?

01:45.647 --> 01:47.348
The, uh, Hollow Leg
Swap-Em-Out?

01:47.416 --> 01:48.749
Yes, exactly.

01:48.817 --> 01:51.452
Fake trombones for a fake band.

01:51.519 --> 01:52.653
Harold Hill!

01:53.470 --> 01:54.555
<i>Music Man?</i>

01:54.622 --> 01:57.090
No, he is not a con man, okay?

01:57.158 --> 01:59.192
You know, he sometimes
used to sell hats.

01:59.260 --> 02:01.261
There you go, boys-- enjoy.

02:01.329 --> 02:02.128
Thanks, Dad.

02:02.196 --> 02:05.529
So many hats.

02:06.400 --> 02:08.633
Okay, technically, they were misprints.

02:10.202 --> 02:11.037
This says:

02:11.105 --> 02:12.905
"Chica Go Bills."

02:12.973 --> 02:16.306
Let's go, guys--
these hats suck.

02:16.376 --> 02:18.978
"Chica Go Bills" is, uh,
actually Spanish

02:19.045 --> 02:21.613
for "Young girl, go Bills."

02:21.681 --> 02:24.583
Who's gonna mess with a guy
who's wearing a hat

02:24.650 --> 02:26.352
that says,
"Young girl, go Bills?"

02:26.419 --> 02:28.354
I mean, the answer is everybody.

02:28.421 --> 02:29.753
They will, they mess with you.

02:31.623 --> 02:34.592
Oh, my... Nick, please
do not angry-fix the sink.

02:34.659 --> 02:36.594
I'm not angry-fixing;
I'm fixing!

02:36.661 --> 02:38.796
You want to know why I'm messed up?

02:38.864 --> 02:40.531
Why I don't trust people?

02:40.599 --> 02:41.799
Why I have anger issues?

02:41.867 --> 02:43.468
Oh, yes, I do want to know.

02:43.535 --> 02:45.435
Why I have the blood pressure
of a hummingbird?

02:48.606 --> 02:50.940
Do you think this
is maybe about your dad?

02:53.511 --> 02:54.611
<i>And so Nickels comes</i>

02:54.678 --> 02:56.713
into my room screaming,
"Daddy, Daddy."

02:56.780 --> 02:58.348
So I go,
"What's wrong?"

02:58.416 --> 03:01.150
He says, "Daddy, I have a tick
at the end of my tinkle."

03:01.218 --> 03:02.918
Oh, my God!

03:02.986 --> 03:05.388
- This is not a story for everyone.
- And sure enough,

03:05.455 --> 03:07.289
there is a tick

03:07.357 --> 03:09.058
at the end of his little penis.

03:09.126 --> 03:10.526
Not a story for this moment.

03:10.593 --> 03:12.061
That's how he got the
nickname "Little Penis."

03:12.129 --> 03:14.096
Oh, stop calling me that.

03:14.164 --> 03:16.484
- What are we gonna do with this guy?
- I have no idea, Pop-Pop.

03:16.500 --> 03:18.533
- Don't call him Pop-Pop.
- That's his nickname.

03:18.600 --> 03:20.435
- The nickname is longer than Walt.
- But that's the nickname

03:20.503 --> 03:21.603
that I gave him.

03:21.604 --> 03:22.703
Yeah, but it's really weird
that you call my dad Pop-Pop.

03:22.771 --> 03:24.572
- I like Pop-Pop.
- You don't get it. You don't get it.

03:24.640 --> 03:26.107
Yeah, fine, just don't
call him Pop-Pop, so...

03:26.175 --> 03:27.975
I think it's time for another drink.

03:28.044 --> 03:29.144
What do you say, gorgeous?

03:29.211 --> 03:30.412
You want to give an old man a hand?

03:30.479 --> 03:31.513
Sure.

03:33.081 --> 03:34.281
I don't know, Nick.

03:34.349 --> 03:35.615
A lot of charm coming

03:35.683 --> 03:36.723
from this end of the booth.

03:36.784 --> 03:38.018
'Cause that's what he does.

03:38.086 --> 03:39.719
He lures you in

03:39.787 --> 03:42.356
with his charm and his moustache
and his perfect hair.

03:42.424 --> 03:44.758
I feel like you need
to talk to him about this.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.026
Right, 'cause I'll just
tell him how I feel,

03:46.094 --> 03:47.627
and everything will be okay

03:47.695 --> 03:49.228
'cause that's really
the way the world works.

03:49.296 --> 03:51.830
Took the words right out
of my mouth, Little Penis.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.533
- It's not a thing.
- I love a good nickname.

03:53.600 --> 03:54.767
Not... not gonna stick.

03:54.834 --> 03:56.001
You know, when Nick
is not working here,

03:56.070 --> 03:57.570
the service is abysmal.

03:57.637 --> 03:59.172
I mean, how many times
did I have to repeat

03:59.239 --> 04:00.706
the words, "Lemon Drop shot"?

04:00.774 --> 04:02.294
Yeah, I think he was making fun of you.

04:02.309 --> 04:03.509
For what?

04:03.577 --> 04:04.910
Working hard and playing hard?

04:04.978 --> 04:06.344
I guess the joke is on me.

04:06.412 --> 04:08.580
Another Indian guy?

04:08.647 --> 04:10.148
- My mom set me up.
- Oh, your mom.

04:10.216 --> 04:11.149
- That's cool.
- Mm-hmm.

04:11.217 --> 04:12.917
Have fun with your, your Devs...

04:12.985 --> 04:15.753
and your...
and your An-Anujs...

04:15.821 --> 04:17.956
or your Deepaks.

04:18.023 --> 04:19.791
Whatever Patel you're dating.

04:19.858 --> 04:21.257
I'm-I'm not sweating it.

04:21.326 --> 04:22.626
His name's Pavun, Pavun Shetty.

04:22.694 --> 04:24.095
What?

04:24.162 --> 04:27.465
- As in, as in "Shetty Solutions"?
- I think so. Why?

04:27.532 --> 04:29.366
They only nailed the
crowd-control logistics

04:29.434 --> 04:31.102
of Bombay's revamped
open-air market.

04:31.169 --> 04:32.136
I thought you weren't sweating it.

04:32.204 --> 04:35.473
I'm not sweating it.
Sweating it.

04:35.540 --> 04:37.707
Killing me with that Drop, dude.

04:39.410 --> 04:41.344
You really seem to care
about Little Nicky.

04:41.412 --> 04:43.079
I mean, look at him.

04:43.147 --> 04:46.480
He looks like Hilary Swank mixed
with a sad, wet dog.

04:47.184 --> 04:48.884
Do you think he's really angry at me?

04:48.952 --> 04:50.386
I think you need to talk to him.

04:51.454 --> 04:53.422
All I'm looking for is a second chance.

04:55.758 --> 04:57.259
You don't happen to believe
in second chances,

04:57.327 --> 04:58.293
do you, Blue Eyes?

04:58.361 --> 05:00.229
Actually, I, um...

05:00.296 --> 05:02.864
I'm a bit of a sucker
for second chances.

05:02.932 --> 05:05.367
They're my first
favorite kind of chance.

05:05.935 --> 05:08.170
Have you ever been to the racetrack?

05:10.591 --> 05:12.724
Back at the tracks with my dad.

05:12.793 --> 05:14.026
When Nick was a kid, he would come

05:14.094 --> 05:15.427
to the track with me all the time.

05:15.495 --> 05:16.628
And if I got in trouble,

05:16.696 --> 05:17.596
he would get me out of it

05:17.664 --> 05:18.864
by doing the Sugar Ray.

05:18.932 --> 05:20.966
- Oh, the Sugar Ray.
- What's a Sugar Ray?

05:21.034 --> 05:23.102
It's when I pretend
to be a diabetic kid

05:23.170 --> 05:24.403
so the man who is threatening

05:24.470 --> 05:26.437
to beat up my father
would run off scared.

05:26.505 --> 05:29.274
You see, we did have
some good times, didn't we?

05:29.341 --> 05:30.341
Now, come on, let's make a bet.

05:30.909 --> 05:31.976
Here you go.

05:32.744 --> 05:33.845
What's the catch?

05:33.913 --> 05:35.546
What catch?
There is no catch.

05:35.614 --> 05:36.747
What possible catch can there be?

05:36.815 --> 05:38.649
All I want you to do is make a bet.

05:39.217 --> 05:40.651
All right, Pop, you want me
to lose your money?

05:40.719 --> 05:42.920
I'll be happy to.

05:44.000 --> 05:50.074
