contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:53.597 --> 05:55.097
Schmidt.

05:55.865 --> 05:57.534
Robby?

05:58.101 --> 05:59.436
Robby, what are, what are
you doing here, man?

05:59.503 --> 06:01.705
- I'm spying on Cece.
- Cece.

06:01.772 --> 06:03.506
You know, I'm still
in love with her, so...

06:03.574 --> 06:06.042
this is pretty much your basic
broken-hearted spying thing.

06:06.609 --> 06:07.710
It's why I got this hat.

06:07.777 --> 06:09.537
Aw, come on, Robby,
you got to get over that.

06:09.579 --> 06:11.046
Wait a second, are you
spying on Cece, too?

06:11.113 --> 06:12.914
No. What?

06:12.982 --> 06:15.317
- Are you still in love with Cece?
- No, that's still...

06:15.385 --> 06:17.052
Yes, I am.

06:17.519 --> 06:18.387
It's killing me.

06:18.455 --> 06:19.955
Me, too!
Bring it in, man.

06:25.594 --> 06:26.894
What are you two doing here?

06:26.962 --> 06:28.730
- Whoa, hey.
- Cece?

06:28.797 --> 06:30.477
- Just nothing, we're just...
- Yeah, you know.

06:32.267 --> 06:33.768
Do you think that she saw me?

06:33.836 --> 06:36.571
What? Of course
she saw you.

06:36.638 --> 06:37.972
Do you think she saw me?

06:38.039 --> 06:39.740
Well, yeah, you don't have a hat on.

06:40.007 --> 06:42.876
Nicky only had one dream
when he was a kid--

06:42.944 --> 06:45.545
to own a family horse.

06:45.613 --> 06:48.946
That is so surprising 'cause
it just doesn't seem like...

06:49.650 --> 06:51.150
Nick hates living things,

06:51.218 --> 06:53.019
so, like, it just doesn't really seem

06:53.087 --> 06:54.753
like in line with
what I know about him.

06:54.821 --> 06:56.922
All right, look...

06:56.990 --> 06:59.892
- I want to buy a horse.
- Uh-huh.

06:59.960 --> 07:02.861
For me and Nick to own together.

07:02.929 --> 07:04.863
- Oh!
- I found this beautiful horse.

07:04.931 --> 07:06.632
- Gorgeous!
- Right.

07:06.700 --> 07:08.300
Me and you are gonna talk the guy down.

07:08.367 --> 07:09.602
I don't know how to do that.

07:09.669 --> 07:11.202
- I'll take care of that.
- Okay.

07:12.537 --> 07:13.471
Hey-ya, Dusty.

07:13.538 --> 07:15.807
Aw, ya gotta be kidding me!

07:15.874 --> 07:16.941
How'd he find me?

07:17.009 --> 07:18.042
Who was that?

07:18.110 --> 07:20.945
Eh, don't worry about him.

07:21.013 --> 07:21.946
What do you know about horses?

07:22.014 --> 07:24.082
I know they're big.

07:24.149 --> 07:25.883
Perfect.

07:25.951 --> 07:27.584
This is a very sad case.

07:27.652 --> 07:28.919
I mean...

07:28.987 --> 07:30.087
My niece, she goes
to veterinary school.

07:30.154 --> 07:31.387
We're all very proud of her.

07:31.455 --> 07:32.689
Top of my class.

07:32.757 --> 07:34.124
So, what do you, uh, what do you think?

07:34.191 --> 07:35.425
Terrible horse.

07:35.493 --> 07:36.660
She's very sickly.

07:36.728 --> 07:39.395
- He. He... He.
- He... He.

07:39.463 --> 07:40.597
Oh!

07:40.665 --> 07:42.898
I wish I had brought my stethoscope.

07:42.966 --> 07:45.300
I'm seeing a lot of split ends.

07:45.368 --> 07:48.470
The mane is totally the wrong
cut for the shape of his face.

07:48.538 --> 07:51.774
So you're saying that this
horse, right now, the way it is,

07:51.842 --> 07:53.876
- will never race again?
- Damn it, Uncle Buck!

07:53.944 --> 07:55.811
This horse will never race again!

07:55.879 --> 07:57.379
Why did you fly me

07:57.447 --> 07:58.747
all the way out from Grenada

07:58.814 --> 08:00.135
if you weren't gonna listen to me?

08:01.984 --> 08:03.952
- Yes, con!
- Shh, shh, shh!

08:04.020 --> 08:05.386
Okay, there are people in life

08:05.454 --> 08:07.555
who you want to be unpredictable.

08:07.623 --> 08:10.956
Your pothead neighbor,
or Vice President Joe Biden.

08:11.093 --> 08:12.894
And then there are people
who you don't want

08:12.962 --> 08:14.962
to be unpredictable, like your dentist,

08:15.030 --> 08:17.364
or, I don't know, your father.

08:17.431 --> 08:19.332
Look, Nick, my dad left
when I was three.

08:19.400 --> 08:20.634
Every single day,

08:20.702 --> 08:22.736
rain or shine, he just never came back.

08:22.804 --> 08:24.371
I wish he'd been a little bit more

08:24.438 --> 08:25.706
unpredictable;
That's all I'm saying.

08:26.674 --> 08:27.541
I hear you.

08:27.608 --> 08:29.676
And yeah, sure, Walt may owe me
a couple hundred bucks,

08:29.677 --> 08:30.544
but it's not a big deal.

08:30.611 --> 08:32.344
My dad owes you money?
How much?

08:32.412 --> 08:34.380
Three, 400... like 1,100 bucks.

08:35.447 --> 08:37.082
Oh, my God, he's with Jess.

08:37.150 --> 08:38.650
He's gonna rip her off.

08:38.719 --> 08:40.318
He's gonna rip her off.

08:40.386 --> 08:42.020
I feel like Cece's making a big mistake

08:42.089 --> 08:43.589
with this Indian guy.

08:44.157 --> 08:46.059
- She should be with somebody like us.
- Totally.

08:46.126 --> 08:47.392
White Guy Power.

08:50.096 --> 08:51.863
Okay, um...

08:51.931 --> 08:53.832
- Cool Guy Power.
- Now you're talking, Robby.

08:53.900 --> 08:55.261
- What are we gonna do?
- I don't know.

08:56.267 --> 08:58.600
I mean, one billion Indian men
is a daunting foe.

08:59.305 --> 09:00.872
Suddenly I feel sympathy for Pakistan.

09:00.940 --> 09:02.674
But it's like they say,

09:02.741 --> 09:04.241
"How do you eat
an elephant, Robby?"

09:04.809 --> 09:05.843
With chopsticks.

09:05.911 --> 09:07.712
- What?
- Slowly, with chopsticks.

09:07.779 --> 09:09.046
- That's-- no-- with chopsticks?!
- In a taco.

09:09.114 --> 09:10.380
- What?
- Elephant tacos.

09:10.448 --> 09:12.116
Elephant tacos?
Who eats elephant tacos?

09:12.184 --> 09:13.684
- That's not even a saying.
- Oh.

09:13.752 --> 09:14.952
One bite at a time, Robby.

09:15.020 --> 09:16.453
- One bite at a time.
- Yes.

09:16.521 --> 09:18.555
One bite at a time.
This is what I'm thinking.

09:18.623 --> 09:21.956
I use my superior powers of
manipulation and persuasion

09:22.426 --> 09:24.027
to get Cece to take you back.

09:24.095 --> 09:27.428
Once we've neutralized
the sub-continental threat,

09:27.897 --> 09:28.898
I smite you.

09:28.966 --> 09:29.966
- What?
- What?

09:30.034 --> 09:32.568
You said you're gonna smite me?

09:32.636 --> 09:34.337
Smite-- defeat gloriously
for Cece's hand.

09:34.404 --> 09:35.738
- No, I know what it means.
- But that's someday.

09:35.772 --> 09:38.907
For now, let's scheme,
my "broheem."

09:38.975 --> 09:40.809
Okay... I just want to reiterate

09:40.877 --> 09:43.645
that I'm not on board with the smiting.

09:43.713 --> 09:45.514
- Whatever.
- But I like the "broheem" thing a lot.

09:45.548 --> 09:46.882
Let's concentrate on the broheem part.

09:46.950 --> 09:48.117
- Concentrate on... okay.
- And smite later.

09:48.184 --> 09:50.485
- Yeah, okay, yeah.
- Cheers, broheem.

09:50.553 --> 09:51.819
You got a great deal.

09:51.887 --> 09:54.355
- Good luck, Doc. - Thanks.
- Dad!

09:54.422 --> 09:56.057
- Hi, boys.
- Can I tell him?

09:56.125 --> 09:57.405
I would rather keep it a secret.

09:57.459 --> 09:58.926
Nick, your dream finally came true.

09:59.494 --> 10:01.229
We got you a horse.

10:01.296 --> 10:03.597
- It's not my dream to own a horse.
- What?

10:03.665 --> 10:05.532
Did you use my friend to buy a horse?

10:05.600 --> 10:06.734
What?
No, I swore you wanted...?

10:06.801 --> 10:07.868
Will you excuse me?
I gotta take this call.

10:07.935 --> 10:09.136
That is unbelievable, Dad.

10:09.203 --> 10:10.403
He had this whole
thing-- he was gonna

10:10.471 --> 10:11.872
name the horse "A Father's Love"
'cause you guys

10:11.939 --> 10:12.906
always wanted to have a horse together.

10:12.974 --> 10:14.207
Tell me you didn't give him money.

10:14.275 --> 10:15.976
Actually, actually,
that's a funny story

10:16.043 --> 10:19.146
because I'm actually an investor in...

10:19.213 --> 10:20.046
God!

10:20.114 --> 10:21.047
God!

10:22.116 --> 10:23.448
Walid, drop dead!

10:23.516 --> 10:24.784
Damn, Pop-Pop.

10:24.851 --> 10:25.918
- Stop calling him Pop-Pop!
- Now, listen,

10:25.986 --> 10:27.186
I already got people standing by

10:27.254 --> 10:29.755
to take the horse off our hands.

10:29.823 --> 10:32.491
Horse semen in Dubai is gold.

10:32.558 --> 10:34.493
No, you can't sell
"A Father's Love."

10:34.560 --> 10:36.896
There's more to "A Father's Love"
than just semen.

10:36.963 --> 10:39.197
Ew, poetic, but ew.

10:39.265 --> 10:40.364
- Dad.
- Dusty, I see you

10:40.432 --> 10:42.100
and we're doing this right now.

10:42.168 --> 10:44.402
- No, no, no, no, no...!
- Dusty!

10:44.469 --> 10:46.271
We got your back, Pop-Pop.

10:46.338 --> 10:47.471
